summary stats quoted in the manuscript

## Between the 2011-2012 and 2018-2019 seasons, individuals enrolled in the US Flu VE Network contributed 61943 visits, among which 55728 0.8996658 met the inclusion criteria of our analyses. Of those included in our analyses, 0.5021892 ( 27986 / 55728 ) of visits were by individuals who had received one dose of the current seasonal influenza vaccine =14 days prior to illness onset date. Among those vaccinated =14 days prior to illness onset, 0.7371543 ( 20630 / 27986 ) of visits were by individuals who were vaccinated at least once in the previous season.
## Surveillance data from the Marshfield Clinic dated back to the 2007-2008 season. In total, 16378 individuals were enrolled between the 2007-2008 season and the 2018-2019 season and contributed 24399 visits.
##  Among these 15459 individuals were included in the main analyses that study the impact of clinical infection. These individuals contributed 21188 visits.
##  Among the 9390 current season vaccinees 0.7840256 (n= 7362 ) were also vaccinated in the previous season, and 0.9093717 (n= 8539 vaccinated in at least one of the three seasons immediately before the enrollment season.
